    "recap_headline": "Army West Point Athletics",
    "recap_text": "WEST POINT, N.Y.\n\u2013 Army West Point baseball was playing for the series on Sunday against the Holy Cross Crusaders, and despite an early 3-0 lead at Doubleday Field, the Black Knights would drop the contest 10-4 and fall in the three-game weekend series, two games to one.\nArmy (7-10, 1-2) took its momentum from Saturday's win and scored three runs in the first inning. After back-to-back walks from\nAddison Ainsworth\nand\nChris Barr\nto open the inning,\nCarter Hewitt\nstepped up with the bases loaded and poked a double just inside the third base foul line, scoring Ainsworth and Barr before a\nThomas Schreck\nsacrifice fly made it a three-run lead for the Black Knights.\nLooking to maintain the lead, starting pitcher\nTrey Ates\nkept the Crusaders off the board in the first and second innings. In the third, he limited the damage to just one run allowed with the bases loaded and nobody out in the frame. After Ates faced the minimum in the fourth, the visitors took their first lead of the game with three runs in the fifth.\nThe junior starting pitcher struck out a pair of batters, pitching four innings and taking a no-decision.\nIn the bottom of the seventh, down a run and having been kept off the board from the first to that point,\nJosiah Overbeek\npoked a two-out double to right field, plating Barr and tying the game at 4-4.\nHowever, Holy Cross would jump back in front with a three run eighth, and pulled away in the ninth with another trio of runs.\nMark Abell\npitched 1.2 innings out of the bullpen, picking up two strikeouts.\nRobbie Penswick\nthrew 2.1 innings and took the loss, with Overbeek and\nJakob Vanderhave\ntossing the ninth.\nThe series loss comes in the Patriot League opening set for both teams, who before the season were picked to finish in the top two of the conference. The loss doesn't end the season series between the sides however, with Army making the return trip to Worcester next month.\nBy the Numbers\n2\n: Hewitt had two RBIs for the second consecutive game.\n2-for-4\n: Dubrule was 2-for-4 at the plate in the series finale.\n2-for-5\n: Barr was 2-for-5 Sunday.\nBlack Knight Notes\nThe lineup card remained mostly intact from Friday and Saturday's contests, but with\nMax McGlone\ntaking the DH spot over\nJohn McKillop\non Sunday.\nAinsworth drew four walks Sunday, the most by a Black Knight in a single game this year. It represented the most amount of walks drawn by an Army player in a single game since\nJustin Lehman\nvs. Georgia State on March 10, 2024.\nNext Up\nArmy is next in action vs. UMass on Tuesday and UAlbany on Wednesday, with both games starting at 3:35 p.m. from Doubleday Field.\nThe Black Knights return to league play next weekend for a three-game series at Lafayette.\nFollow the Black Knights\nFollow Army Baseball on X\n@ArmyWP_Baseball\nand on Instagram\n@armywp_baseball\n. Fans can also like\nArmy West Point Athletics\non Facebook and learn more about baseball and other programs at\ngoarmywestpoint.com\n."
  },
